# Frontend API usage

- **Client**: Use the shared axios `api` instance from `src/api/client` (base URL from `VITE_API_BASE_URL`). Do not scatter raw `fetch` to the API unless there is an existing pattern (e.g. streaming).
- **Errors**: ASP.NET often returns ProblemDetails (`title`, `detail`, `status`). When handling errors, read **`detail`** (and fallbacks) like existing `problemDetail` helpers—do not assume Axios `error.response.data.message` alone.
- **Auth**: The client should already attach Bearer tokens where configured; new authenticated calls go through the same `api` instance.
- **Query params**: Match server names (`instrumentToken`, `interval`, `model`, etc.). Optional params may be omitted rather than sent empty when the server treats null as default.
- **Displayed lists**: When the API promises “newest first” or UX requires it, sort explicitly (e.g. by `predictedAt`) rather than assuming array order from merges or localStorage.
- **Extract shared helpers**: Prefer one shared `problemDetail`/`parseProblemDetails` in `src/utils/` when adding new pages rather than copying another 30-line helper.
